</div>

<!--About paragraph regarding history of company-->
<div class="row" style="padding: 30px; font-family: 'Lucida Bright';  line-height: 30px; font-size: 18px">
    <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-2" style="border-right: 2px solid black">
        <p>
            Dunk 'Em was founded by four returned missionaries who wanted to bring knowledge to prospective
            servants of the Lord! They founded this company with the simple goal of helping young men and women learn
            about serving missions all over the globe and discover answers to questions they might have.
            The four founding members are Josh Harris, Bryce LeFevre, Michael Anderson and Josh Simpson who all met as juniors
            in the Management Information Systems Program at the Marriott School of Business at Brigham Young University in
            Provo, UT. Greg Anderson, Professor of the Business Programming class where these four met, said about them that
            they were "The greatest group of students he has ever taught" (<span style="font-style: italic">citation not found</span>).
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <p>
            One thing these four returned missionaries had in common was a love of their missionary service and the areas where they served.
            They decided that they wanted to share that excitement for their missions with others and in 2017 founded "Dunk 'Em."
            Dunk 'Em takes the combined knowledge of thousands of returned missionaries who answer questions posted by curious visitors,
            future missionaries or the worried mothers of those future missionaries... With great pride and 3 weeks of company history, these
            innovators continue to push with their original goal of bringing mission wisdom to those who seek!
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

